SPICY PEANUT VEGETABLE SOUP 🍜 
.
This recipe is DAMN GOOD! It’s rich, flavorful, and full of umami 😛 If you need a quick and easy soup recipe for the cold weather give this a shot:
INGREDIENTS:
1 sweet potato, peeled and cubed
1 large shallot, diced
1 cup kale, roughly chopped
5-6 mushrooms, chopped
1/3 cup creamy peanut butter
3 garlic cloves
3 stalks green onions, chopped
1 juice of lime
1 serrano, minced
1 14oz can full fat coconut milk
1 tbsp gochujang
2 tbsp soy sauce
4 cups chicken or vegetable stock
.
DIRECTIONS:
1) Heat a large dutch oven or pot over medium heat. Add a little neutral oil.
2) Add shallots, garlic, chili, and green onion. Saute for 2-3 minutes.
3) Add gochujang paste, incorporate well for 2 minutes. 
4) Add coconut milk, peanut butter, stock, soy sauce, pinch of salt and pepper. Mix well and bring to a boil.
5) Once boiling, reduce the heat to a simmer. Add potatoes and cook for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
6) Add kale, mushrooms, and juice of 1 lime. Cook for 5 minutes. Taste and adjust seasoning if needed. Serve warm with fresh green onions, and squeeze of lime. #vitacost #healthycooking

CHOCOFLAN BUNDT CAKE 🍰 
.
This was a fun recipe to create! I’m a huge fan of flan and I came across a recipe that combined it with a Bundt cake. Winner Winner! The texture was so different and delicious. The best of both worlds and I highly recommended making your caramel from scratch 🔥 #vitacost #recipes #chocolate 
.
INGREDIENTS:
For the cake:
1 1/2 cups ap flour
1/2 cup unsalted butter room temperature
1/4 cup of homemade or store bought caramel
1 cup light brown sugar
1/4 cup dutch process cocoa powder
1 large egg
1 tsp baking powder
3/4 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp sea salt
1/2 cup water
1/2 cup whole milk
. 
For the Flan
5 large eggs
1 14oz can sweetened condensed milk
2 tsp vanilla extract
1 cup whole milk or half and half
.
DIRECTIONS:
For the cake
1) Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 10-12 cup bundt pan with room temperature butter. Make sure to get all crevices to avoid sticking. Add 1/4 caramel sauce to the bottom of the bundt pan and set to the side.
2) In a large bowl or stand mixer add sugar and butter until light and fluffy. (2-3 minutes). Add egg and beat until well combined.
3) In a medium bowl, whisk flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt. Add 1/2 dry ingredients to the wet mixture. Combine well. 
4) Pour the batter into the bundt cake pan on top of caramel. 
For the flan
1) In a large bowl whisk eggs, condensed milk, and vanilla until well combined. Add milk slowly and whisk. Slowly pour the flan mixture into the bundt cake pan. 
2) Tightly cover the top with foil and place into a large roasting pan. Carefully transfer to the oven and add enough hot water to the roasting pan until it reaches about halfway up the pan. 
3) Bake for 60-70 minutes or until a tester inserted into the center comes out clean. Carefully transfer the bundt cake pan to a wire rack and uncover. Allow to cool for 1 hour. Refrigerate for 2-3 hours or best overnight. 
4) To loosen the cake, add to a large bowl of warm water for a few minutes. Use a large plate to put on top of the cake pan. With 2 hands flip the pan over and slowly remove the bundt pan. Enjoy!

AIR FRIED COCONUT SHRIMP 🍤 
with sweet and spicy chili crisp sauce
.
If you guys love shrimp then definitely give these a try! I have been loving my air fryer lately and experimenting with lots of fun recipes. This was FIRE 🔥 
.
INGREDIENTS:
1lb large wild shrimp, devein and shell removed
3/4 cup ap flour
1/2 cup unsweetened coconut flakes
1/2 cup panko breadcrumbs
2 eggs, beaten
Sea salt and pepper
. 
For the sauce:
1/2 cup sweet chili sauce
1 tbsp spicy chili crisp
1/2 tbsp rice wine vinegar
1 tbsp fresh chopped cilantro 
.
1) Use 3 different bowls and create a dredge station. Fill 1 bowl with flour, 1 bowl with coconut flakes and panko, 1 bowl with eggs.
2) Add a pinch of salt and pepper to the coconut flakes and panko.
3) Dredge each shrimp into flour, then egg, then coconut/panko mix. Make sure to shake off the excess flour and egg after each dredge. Place on the rack of the air fryer and repeat the process until all of the shrimp are dredged and coated.
4) Set the air fryer to 390 degrees for 3 minutes. Lightly spray the shrimp with cooking oil then place in the fryer. After 3 minutes flip the shrimp, spray with cooking oil and set temp to 400 degrees for 2 minutes. After 5 minutes the shrimp should be crunchy and delicious.
5) Sprinkle it with a little sea salt and dip it in that amazing sauce 👅

IRISH POTATO PIE 🥧☘️
.
Potatoes, bacon, cheese, cream, chives, puff pastry… need I say more? 😜👀 The perfect recipe for St Patty’s! 
.
Ingredients:
3 large russet potatoes
1 sheet puff pastry, thawed
1/2 white onion, diced
5 strips bacon
1/2 cup heavy cream
1/2 cup cheddar cheese
1/2 cup Irish cheddar cheese
Salt and pepper
Dill
Chives for garnish
.
Directions:
•Preheat oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
•Heat a skillet on medium heat. Add bacon and cook until rendered and brown. Remove from the pan.
•Peel potatoes and cut in half length wise. Cut thin slices in the shape of half circles.
•Add onions to pan and cook in the grease for 2 minutes. Add potatoes, few sprigs of dill, salt and pepper. Cook for 2-3 minutes mixing occasionally. 
•Roll the puff pastry out once or twice just to give it shape. Lightly butter or grease a tart or pie dish. Lay the puff pastry over the dish and press into the pan. If there is excess dough hanging over, you can trim it off. Crimp the edges of the pastry to form a crust.
•Fill the dish with the potato mixture. Try and spread the potatoes evenly across the dish and create layers. Top with chopped bacon and heavy cream.
•Bake for 20 minutes then raise temperature to 420 degrees. Top with cheese and bake for another 15 minutes or until golden brown.
•Remove and allow to cool for 10-15 minutes before slicing. Top with sour cream and chives.

You bettah believe it’s homemade compound buttah! 🧈

Compound butter is a unique butter used to finish a dish by enhancing it with complimentary flavor. 😋 This elevated butter is added in the last steps of recipe creation to imbue it with extra flavor. Seasoned with garlic, shallot, orange and a bit of jalapeño and cilantro, the flavor combo in this recipe is beyond wonderful with seafood, meat and veggies. You’ll find that it’s inspirational to have some on hand to explore and enjoy. Stash it in the freezer and use a slice whenever you’re feeling creative.

INGREDIENTS
½ cup (1 stick) salted butter softened
1 clove garlic minced
1 Tbsp. shallot minced
1 orange zest and juice
1/2 jalapeño minced
1 Tbsp. cilantro minced

DIRECTIONS
1️⃣ In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Use fork to mash butter and mix until well incorporated.
2️⃣ Lay out large piece of parchment paper or plastic wrap and place butter in middle. With spatula or spoon, roughly lengthen and shape butter into thick log shape, fold one side of parchment or plastic wrap over butter and begin rolling until tight. (Note: Rolling against counter or cutting board will create smooth sides and even shape.)
3️⃣ Place in freezer for 30 minutes or refrigerate at least 2 hours to harden prior to slicing.

Not sure if making banana bread has ever looked more seductive. 🍌🤤

Level up breakfast with this heavenly and surprisingly simple banana bread French toast by @briewilly: 🍞 Topped with banana slices caramelized in brown sugar and butter, this is one of those recipes that’s so indulgent it’s almost too good to believe. 😋 Start with your favorite banana bread and follow a couple of quick steps to impeccably stylish good taste.

INGREDIENTS
4 slices banana bread 2 inches thick
2 eggs
1/4 cup milk
1 Tbsp. crème brûlée creamer optional
1 tsp. cinnamon
2 bananas 2-inch slices
4 Tbsp. butter
1 Tbsp. brown sugar

DIRECTIONS 
1. In large mixing bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, cream and cinnamon. Dredge each slice of banana bread and let soak 10 seconds.
2. In pan over medium heat, heat one tablespoon butter. Arrange bread in pan. After about 1 minute, or once toast is golden-brown, flip and cook for another minute. Once all bread is cooked, remove to plate. (Note: Do not overcrowd pan.)
3. In clean pan over medium heat, melt 2 tablespoons butter and add brown sugar to create caramel sauce. Add bananas and caramelize for 2 minutes. Flip bananas and cook another minute. Remove from pan.
4. To serve, drizzle caramel sauce on plates. Add slice of French toast and top with bananas. Use powdered sugar or syrup, if desired.

CARAMEL TURTLE BROWNIE PIE 👀
.
I am the worlds worst baker but I do love trying new things. This recipe was fairly easy and turned out great! The homemade graham cracker crust was a great addition to the rich gooey brownie. Enjoy my friends and happy Friday!
.
Ingredients:
(for the crust)
11 Honey Graham Crackers
2 tbsp organic sugar
6 tbsp melted salted butter
.
(for the brownie)
1/2 cup ap flour
3/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder
2 eggs
1 cup granulated sugar
2 tbsp coconut oil
1/2 cup unsalted butter (melted)
2 tsp vanilla extract
1/4 tsp sea salt
caramel (store bought or homemade)
whipped cream
pecans
.
Directions
1) Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
2) Begin making the graham cracker crust. Add graham crackers to a food processor. Blend until it's a fine crumb texture. Add to a large bowl, mix in the sugar. Add melted butter and combine well. The texture should be similar to wet sand.
3) Add crust mix to a 9 inch pie dish. Begin pressing and patting the crust into the dish making it compact. Once you have a nice crust formed, set to the side.
4) Begin making the brownie, in a large bowl add sugar, coconut oil, and melted butter. Whisk well. Add eggs and vanilla extract. Combine well. 
5) Add flour, cocoa powder, and salt. Use a spatula and mix well. Add brownie mix to the pie dish.
6) Bake for 35-40 minutes just until the center is slightly gooey and will continue to cook as it cools. Add a layer of caramel to the top of the brownie. Allow the pie to sit at room temperature for 20 minutes or so. Top with whipped cream, drizzle of caramel, and pecans. Enjoy!

APPLE & GOAT CHEESE EMPANADAS 🍎 
.
These make you feel like Snoop, so fly and wanna dance 😮‍💨 I’ve always loved the combination of apples and cheese. The perfect sweetness from the sautéed apples in butter, brown sugar, and cinnamon stuffed into a empanada dough and topped with tangy creamy goat cheese 🔥 Say no more… 😉
.
INGREDIENTS 
•3 apples of your choice (I used Gala)
•10-12 empanada discs (homemade or store bought)
•1/2 stick salted butter 
•2 tbsp brown sugar
•1 tsp cinnamon
•6oz crumbled goat cheese
.
1) preheat oven OR Dutch oven with oil depending on if you’re baking or frying. (I used the fried method)
2) Peel and cut apples into small cubes about 1/4 inch
3) Heat a pan over medium heat and add butter. Once melted add brown sugar. Once combined, add apples and cinnamon. Sauté for 3-4 minutes until softened then remove pan from the heat. 
4) Heat oil for frying to 375 degrees. Add about 2 tbsp of apple filling to an empanada disc, top with a few crumbles of goat cheese. Fold in half and crimp the edges to seal the dough. 
5) Add prepped empanadas to hot oil, cook in small batches maybe 2-3 at a time. Fry for about 60-90 seconds until golden brown. Repeat process for all.
6) Optional, toss in cinnamon sugar and serve!

HOLIDAY CROSTINI: Whipped goat and feta cheese, spiced candied walnuts, pickled green apple 🎄🤌
.
INGREDIENTS:
1 fresh baguette, sliced into 1/2 inch rounds
1 oz crumbled goat cheese
2 oz crumbled feta cheese
2 granny smith apples, julienne cut
1/4 cup apple cider vinegar
1/2 tbsp lemon juice
2 tbsp olive oil
salt and pepper
candied nuts:
2 cups raw walnuts
2 tbsp ghee butter
1/4 cup white sugar
1/2 tsp ground cloves
1 tsp cinnamon
1/2 tsp sea salt
.
1) Add prepared apples to a bowl. Add apple cider vinegar, pinch of salt, splash of water. Mix with hands and place to the side. This will quickly pickle and add some zing. 
2) To a food processor, add goat cheese, feta cheese, lemon juice, 2 tbsp olive oil, pinch of salt and pepper. Pulse until well combined, add to a bowl and set to the side.
3) In a pan, add a little olive oil over medium heat. Add baguette slices and top with pinch of salt, flip after 1 minute. Once golden, remove from the pan.
4) Clean the pan and wipe it dry. Over medium heat, add raw walnuts. Mix and toast for 1 minute then add ghee, sugar, clove, cinnamon, and salt. Mix well and allow the butter and sugar to caramelize toast. Cook for about 5 minutes, then remove from the pan to cool.
5)  Assemble crostini, add a good dollop of the cheese mix to a slice of bread, then add a few walnuts and pickled apples. Finish with a drizzle of olive oil and fresh cracked pepper. @vitacost #recipes

SLOW SMOKED SALMON
WALNUT CAPER OLIVE VINAIGRETTE 🔥
.
Flaaaavor bomb! You can cook this in the oven or on the grill at 275 degrees for 30 minutes then finish at 350 for 10 minutes. The result is tender, flakey flavorful fish especially with the crunchy sweet and salty vinaigrette. Stay hungry my friends! 😉👊
.
INGREDIENTS:
2lb whole fresh salmon filet
2 tbsp olive oil
1/2 juice of lime
1 tbsp honey
1 tbsp paprika
2 tsp sea salt
1 tsp cracked pepper
.
for the vinaigrette 
3/4 cup olive oil
1/2 juice of lemon
1 tsp fresh cracked pepper
1/2 cup flat leaf parsley, chopped
2 tbsp dill, chopped
1/4 cup walnuts, lightly toasted and chopped
1/4 cup pitted castelvetrano olives, chopped
1 tbsp capers, chopped
1/2 tbsp red wine vinegar
Pinch of salt
.
DIRECTIONS:
1) Preheat the oven or grill to 275 degrees. In a small bowl, add 2 tbsp olive oil, juice of lime, paprika, salt, and pepper. Mix well then coat the fish. Slow roast for 25-30 minutes. For the last 10 minutes, drizzle a little honey over the fish and bake at 350 until the thickest part of the filet reaches 125-130 degrees internal. Remove and rest.
2) In a bowl, add all ingredients for the vinaigrette. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.
3) Spoon a generous amount of vinaigrette on top of the fish and serve tableside! Enjoy.

CHICKEN PICCATA w/ LEMON & PARM LINGUINE 🍝 
.
This was FIRE my friends. Save the recipe and remember to cook with some DOPE music 🎶 
.
Ingredients:
4 boneless skinless chicken breast
1 cup ap flour
3 tbsp cold butter
1/2 cup chicken stock
1 tbsp capers with juice
1/2 lemon, sliced
1 box Linguine pasta
Olive oil
Salt and pepper
Parsley
Parmesan Cheese

Directions:
1) Preheat the oven to 400 degrees.
2) Add a little salt and pepper to both sides of the chicken breast. Dredge in flour and set to the side.
3) Heat a cast iron skillet or large pan to medium high heat. Add about 2 tbsp of olive oil.
4) Once oil is hot, add chicken breast and sear for about 90 seconds per side. Remove from the pan.
5) Add chicken stock, capers, butter, and the juice from 2 slices of lemon. Mix well and make sure to scrape any brown bits.
6) Add chicken breast back to the pan and place in the oven until it hits 165 degrees. Remove chicken from pan and reduce sauce for a few mins until thickened. 
7) Add pasta to boiling salted water. Cook for 9-10 minutes. Remove and add to a bowl with a drizzle of olive oil and parmesan cheese.
8) Once pasta is finished, begin plating. Add pasta, chicken breast, chopped parsley, fresh parmesan, and top with a little bit of the pan sauce. Enjoy!

One of my favorite breakfasts since I was a kid were pancakes. I grew up on the box blends but today I love making them from scratch and sometimes a little bit healthy. These were so tasty just like that syrup shot 📸🥵 Happy Friday!

Ingredients:
1 cup buckwheat flour
3/4 cup oat flour
1 egg, beaten
1 tsp cinnamon
1 cup milk of choice, I used 1%
3 tbsp coconut sugar
1 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp sea salt
Olive oil
.
Directions:
1) In a large mixing bowl add flours, cinnamon, coconut sugar, baking soda, and sea salt. Mix well.
2) Add egg and 1 cup of milk to the bowl and incorporate well. Add more milk if needed for a smooth consistent texture.
3) Heat a non-stick pan over medium heat. Add about 1 tbsp of olive oil. When hot, add 1/2 cup of pancake mix to the pan. Work in batches.
4) Top with butter, fruit, or syrup and enjoy!
